{"name": "bilby-numpyro", "metadata": {"name": "bilby-numpyro", "version": "0.0.1", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["arviz", "bilby", "jax", "numpy", "numpyro"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1732233503}, "documentation": ["# bilby-numpyro\n\nSampler plugin for using `numpyro` samplers with `Bilby`\n\n`bilby-numpyro` is a sampler plugin for using `numpyro` samplers with `Bilby` likelihoods and priors.\nAny likelihood that uses only `JAX` JIT-compilable functions/classes works automatically.\n\n## Usage\n\nThe sampler should always be given as `numpyro` regardless of which sampler (e.g., `HMC`, `NUTS`) is actually being used.\nThe sampler is specified with `sampler_name` and any sampler keyword arguments should be passed in the usual way to\n`bilby.core.sampler.run_sampler` for example\n\n```python\nrun_sampler(\n    ...,\n    sampler=\"numpyro\",\n    sampler_name=\"NUTS\",\n    num_warmup=500,\n    num_samples=1000,\n)\n```\n\nThis has not been tested with `numpyro` parallelisation.\n\n## Limitations\n\nThe likelihood class you use should be JIT compilable with `JAX`.\nGenerally, this will be the case if you use `jax.numpy` and `jax.scipy` instead of `numpy`/`scipy`.\n\nSome `Bilby` priors have direct equivalents in `numpyro` and so we use those automatically.\nYou will see logged warnings if a prior is not available and a `Uniform` prior over the same range will be used instead.\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "tests.test_bilby_integration", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "tests.test_bilby_integration.model", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "m", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "c", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_bilby_integration.bilby_likelihood", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_bilby_integration.bilby_priors", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_bilby_integration.sampler_kwargs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_bilby_integration.test_run_sampler", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "bilby_likelihood", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bilby_priors", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tmp_path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sampler_kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "bilby_numpyro", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "bilby_numpyro.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "bilby_numpyro.utils.bilby_to_numpyro_prior", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bilby_numpyro.utils.bilby_to_numpyro_priors", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "priors", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bilby_numpyro.utils.generic_bilby_likelihood_function", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "likelihood", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "parameters", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "use_ratio", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bilby_numpyro.utils.construct_numpyro_model", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "likelihood", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "priors", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "likelihood_func", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bilby_numpyro.utils.sample_prior", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "priors", "type": null, "default": null}, {"na